{
  "stem": "14060.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he decided, in a Solomon-type of decision, that they will have to create in the certain part of that town two walls, human walls, one where the Jews are and one where the non-Jews are.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And whichever side the child is going to go, that's where it belongs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, the story goes on that the child came-- I don't know, a three- or four-year-old child-- and recognized an aunt or whoever and went there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that was so.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "What I'm trying to bring out is that whilst the Esterhazys, as such, were liberal to Jews, the entire atmosphere was far from liberal.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I presume, in other parts of Europe, probably it wasn't much better either.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now the-- my maternal side of the family-- the family name is Holzer, H-O-L-Z-E-R-- also similarly came to that part of Hungary in around about the 1700s, 1800s.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And according to the anecdotes of the family, they originated from the Rhineland.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Bearing the name of Holzer would probably justify it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they lived in a certain part of the next county, which is called Vas Megye, spelled V-A-S, and moved into the capital of that county called Szombathely, which is 60 kilometers south of Sopron, the town I was born in.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And having come, again, from agriculture background and having liquidated their assets there-- went into the business of, of a flour mill, which they were very, very successful.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In fact, my grandfather, for many-- most of the years I remember, was a president of the community and a very charitable man and known to be a, a very wealthy man.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I'm giving you basically the background of the family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother had two sisters and four brothers.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
